channel.title: Should I Get This Processor?
channel.description:
Is this processor worth it? I will use it on my laptop that currently has i3, is it any good for running bots on?
http://www.amazon.co.uk/INTEL-I7-2600K-3400MHz-LGA1155-Desktop/dp/B004FA8NOQ/ref=sr_1_9?s=computers&ie=UTF8&qid=1347749256&sr=1-9
I have about 1/2 of the money, my birthday is in 1 and a half weeks, so like I reckon I`ll have enough, or should I get an i5 processor, theres only £25, not really bothered, my laptop heats up quickly, is that to do with the fan or processor, its a hp pavillion dv6 with an i3 processor, should I get i7, and then buy a nvidia graphics card...
Please post below, and also tell me what makes it heat up really quickly, I`m sure it only has one fan. Dclawed

item.title: Should I Get This Processor?
item.dc:creator: @Nothing1 -Nothing
item.description:
@Nothing1 wrote:

You’re not supposed to play on bed/other soft surface with a laptop because it will block the fan making it not cool down properly, and in time it will cause heating problems due to it taking lots of dust/hair/fibre in.

There’s a reason why they recommend to use your laptop on flat surface like table.

item.dc:creator: @Ruby_Forums_Coder Ruby
item.description:
@Ruby_Forums_Coder wrote:

dclawed:

Ok, will open it up and sort stuff out, and I normally sit on my bed, I always like freeze etc, and after playing rs for 1 hr it heats up like hell, whys this? I sometimes sit on the table, but I usually sit on my bed. Im probably going to buy the i7, although I dont have amazon account, or any debit cards, just going to get rsgp :L

Well you can imagine if you have a fan sucking in air from your bed sheets and what not its going to be picking up a lot of fibres, not all of these exit and therefore clog up the internal part of your cooling system.
